vioral sciences—that would provide the basis for nursing practice. Their efforts transformed nursing’s labor into a valuable site of knowledge production and proved how the application of their knowledge was integral to improving patient outcomes. Exploring the knowledge claims, strategies, and politics involved as academic nurses negotiated their roles and nursing’s future, Dr. Nurse highlights how state-supported health centers have profoundly shaped nursing education and health care delivery.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aNursesxEducationzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aNursingxStudy and teaching (Graduate)zUnited StatesxHistory. 0aNursingxStudy and teachingzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aNursingzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 7aMEDICAL / General.2bisacsh  anursing, academic health center, health policy, nursing science, biomedical science, research university, nursing education, clinical research, gender, feminism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022 Englishz978311099319608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022z9783110993134oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107665090 cprintz978022682288440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226822891423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226822891/original  a978-3-11-076650-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099319-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-